medreses. He also explores the reactions and changing attitudes of Islamic intellectuals to the religious policies of the secular republic, and provides a better understanding of the changes in the relationship between religion and state. Exposing division within the religious establishment, this book illuminates the ulema's long-lasting legacies still in evidence in Turkey today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aIslam and statezTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 0aIslamzTurkeyxFunctionariesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMuslim scholarszTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 0aReligion. 0aSecularismzTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 0aUlamazTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804777766zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804777766423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804777766.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles